name: What Has Become Of Me? | P0038 #pennydrops
description:
'My name was Jane Coombs. I stole a petticoat worth 1 shilling and was sentenced to 1 month hard labor on 13th August 1859. I was 13 years old.'

--

This piece forms part of our artwork for Prison Residences at Shepton Mallet Prison, UK, 18/09/21-03/10/21. Some of this edition will be reserved for attendees of the residency.
